### 3.11 AI Reference Mode & Lead Generation Modes (New)

#### Purpose

Allow users to choose whether to use AI reference materials or not during lead generation. This ensures flexibility across different user roles (sales, presales, research).

---

#### Modes Supported

##### 1. Full AI Mode (AI Reference ON)

User provides:

* Document (PDF/DOCX)
* URL / website
* Product from Master Product

Behavior:

* AI parses reference
* Infers:

  * target industry
  * sub-industry
  * buyer persona
  * use case
* Drives advanced lead scoring

Use Case:

* Presales
* Solution architect
* Complex products

---

##### 2. Manual Mode (AI Reference OFF)

User provides:

* Product name
* Optional industry / keyword

Behavior:

* System uses:

  * keyword matching
  * basic rule-based filtering
* Optional lightweight AI scoring (no deep context)

Use Case:

* Fast prospecting
* Sales team usage

---

##### 3. Hybrid Mode (Recommended Default)

User provides:

* Product name
* Optional industry

AI assists:

* refine persona
* refine use case
* generate pitch suggestion
* light scoring

Use Case:

* Balanced speed vs intelligence

---

#### UI/UX Flow

Add toggle before lead generation:

* Use AI Reference (toggle)

  * If ON:

    * Upload document
    * Input URL
    * Select from product master
  * If OFF:

    * Skip AI parsing

---

#### Processing Flow

Full AI Mode:

* Product → AI parsing → product profile → scoring engine → leads

Manual Mode:

* Product → keyword/industry mapping → leads → optional AI scoring

Hybrid Mode:

* Product → partial AI enrichment → leads → scoring

---

#### Data Model Additions

Add fields:

* use_ai_reference (boolean)
* ai_mode (enum: full_ai, hybrid, manual)
* ai_reference_source_type (document, url, master_product)
* ai_reference_id
* ai_processing_status (pending, processing, completed, failed)

---

#### Governance & Control

* Allow admin to set default mode
* Allow restriction of Full AI mode for certain roles
* Log AI reference usage in audit log

