### 7.6 Lead Source Confidence Score

For every enriched field, track:

* Source type
* Channel type under the selected lead source
* Confidence level
* Last verified date

Lead source and channel type master data must be editable from Settings and persisted in PostgreSQL. The Leads list and create/edit flow must expose both fields so sales users can classify whether a lead came from Google Maps, manual entry, import, referral, WhatsApp, web, or another configured source, then classify the deeper channel beneath that source.

### 7.6.1 Lead Closing Amount Tracking

For each lead, track:

* Estimated closing amount
* Realized closing amount

Both values must be stored in PostgreSQL and visible on the Leads list so pipeline value and actual closed value can be compared without opening the lead detail page.

### 7.6.2 Currency and Number Formatting

The platform must provide database-backed currency and numeric display settings:

* World currency master data
* Active platform currency
* Thousands separator
* Decimal separator
* Decimal precision
* Currency symbol position and spacing

All visible operational amount and number formatting should consume the shared formatter backed by this setting rather than hardcoded locale, currency code, or separator rules.

